N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 6 ยง 193.2 - Protected trees

State Regulations

The following trees, by reason of their rarity, uniqueness, scarcity or endangered status, shall be protected pursuant to section
9-1503
of the Environmental Conservation

Law: Balmville Tree (eastern cottonwood x carolina popular) located at the
intersection of River Road, Balmville Road and Grand Avenue in the
unincorporated community of Balmville, Town of Newburgh, Orange
